===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
In the {{w|oracle bone script}}, an {{Han compound|人|⿴囗⿱人仌|t1=person|t2=bamboo mat|ls=ic|nocap=y}} – a person resting on a mat. Sometimes a house ({{zh-l|*宀}}) was added.

Later the pictogram of the bamboo mat became {{zh-l|*㐁}} or {{zh-l|*𠀬}}, and eventually came to be written {{zh-l|*百}}.

Contrast {{zh-l|*寒}}.

===Etymology===
; “To stay overnight; lodge > night; mansion of the zodiac [i.e. the Sun's lodging stations]”
: Probably related to Austroasiatic: cf. {{cog|okz||*ruk|to take cover or shelter}} > {{cog|km|ជ្រុក||shelter; refuge}}, {{cog|km|ស្រុក||settlement; village}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). {{zh-ref|Benedict (1972)}} relates it to the Tibeto-Burman terms listed in the etymology of {{och-l|夜|night}}, however the phonetics is difficult to reconcile in the current reconstructions.

